OL,3,COne in six beds left vacant in some
OL,4,Cprivate Guernsey care homes
OL,6,FAnna Reeve has been caring for her 91-
OL,7,Fyear-old mother for two years and
OL,8,Fdescribes how she would have to use
OL,9,Fher and her sister's savings to pay
OL,10,Ffor a care home place like she did for
OL,11,Fher father.
OL,13,FShe explains: "I suppose the
OL,14,Fdifficulty is no one has a crystal
OL,15,Fball. We knew that Dad was at end-of-
OL,16,Flife care but if you've got a
OL,17,Fcondition that is going to ramble on
OL,18,Fand on then how many years is that
OL,19,Fgoing to be for?
